{"title_page": "Rib Hillis", "text_new": "{{BLP IMDb refimprove|date=September 2009}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Rib Hillis\n| image       =\n| imagesize   =\n| caption     =\n| birth_name  = Robert Duane Hillis\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1970|11|21}}\n| birth_place = Suffern, New York\n| website     =\n| occupation  = Model, Actor\n| spouse      = {{ubl|[[Elena Grinenko]] (August 2012)}}\n}}\n'''Robert Duane'' \"''Rib''\" ''Hillis''' (born November 21, 1970) is an American [[Model (person)|model]] and [[actor]].\n\n== Biography ==\nBorn as Robert Duane Hillis in [[Suffern, New York]] and grew up in [[Newton, Massachusetts]] with his parents, two sisters and brother.  Hillis graduated from [[Newton South High School]]. He picked up his unusual nickname \"Rib\" while in the third grade playing with frogs, and enjoyed the sounds that they make.\n\nHillis married a woman four days after their first date but separated in 2008. They have twins. On August 17, 2012, he married ballroom dancer, world champion and former ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'' pro, [[Elena Grinenko]].\n\n=== Modeling ===\nDuring his junior year at the [[University of Colorado at Boulder|University of Colorado]] in Boulder, he was discovered by a modeling agent. Since college, he's been a much sought-after model, working in Milan, Paris, Barcelona, London, Sydney, New York, Miami and Los Angeles for such publications as Uomo [[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]], [[GQ]], [[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]] and [[Men's Health]], as well as countless national and international commercials. In addition, he landed various print campaigns for [[Versace]], [[Armani]] and Catalyst Cologne.\n\nHe appeared on an episode of ''[[America's Next Top Model, Cycle 4]]'' in 2005 as a lingerie model in the episode \"The Girl Who Pushes Tyra Over The Edge\".\n\n=== Acting ===\nReturning to the U.S. in spring of 1996, Hillis moved to Los Angeles and landed a role on an episode of ''[[Baywatch Nights]]'' as Jeds.\n\nHis most notable role as an actor came in 2015 on ''General Hospital''\u2019s spin-off ''[[Port Charles]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soapcentral.com/pc/whoswho/jake.php|accessdate=April 18, 2016|work=SoapCentral|title=Jake Marshak}}</ref> as [[Jake Marshak|Dr. Jake Marshak]]. He was on the show from 1997\u20131998 and in May 2006, he substituted for [[Eric Martsolf]] as [[Ethan Winthrop]] on ''[[Passions]]'' when Martsolf took paternity leave for his newborn twin sons. Moreover, he has appeared in dozens of television shows such as ''[[Ugly Betty]]'', ''[[Two and a Half Men]]'', ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation|CSI]]'' and ''[[CSI: Miami]]''. He also has a starring role in the feature film ''[[Propiedad Ajena]].''\n\nHillis played the leading role in the Syfy feature film ''[[Piranhaconda]]'' in 2012.\nHe played Val Walker in ''[[Cowboys vs Dinosaurs]]'' in 2012.\n\n=== Reality Television ===\n\nHillis has done two home improvement/building shows, ''Model Citizen'' and ''[[Get a Grip]]''.\n\nIn the Fall 2007 TV season, Hillis joined the design team on ABC's ''[[Extreme Makeover: Home Edition]]''.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|id=0385032|name=Rib Hillis}}\n* [http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/rib-hillis/265299 Rib Hillis in TV Guide]\n* [http://abc.go.com/primetime/xtremehome/index?pn=bios#t=designer&d=32781 Rib Hillis at ABC]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hillis, Rib}}\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:American male soap opera actors]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male models from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:People from Suffern, New York]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP IMDb refimprove|date=September 2009}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Rib Hillis\n| image       =\n| imagesize   =\n| caption     =\n| birth_name  = Robert Duane Hillis\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1970|11|21}}\n| birth_place = Suffern, New York\n| website     =\n| occupation  = Model, Actor\n| spouse      = {{ubl|[[Elena Grinenko]] (August 2012)}}\n}}\n'''Robert Duane Hillis''' (born November 21, 1970) is an American [[Model (person)|model]] and [[actor]].\n\n== Biography ==\nBorn as Robert Duane Hillis in [[Suffern, New York]] and grew up in [[Newton, Massachusetts]] with his parents, two sisters and brother.  Hillis graduated from [[Newton South High School]]. He picked up his unusual nickname \"Rib\" while in the third grade playing with frogs, and enjoyed the sounds that they make.\n\nHillis married a woman four days after their first date but separated in 2008. They have twins. On August 17, 2012, he married ballroom dancer, world champion and former ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'' pro, [[Elena Grinenko]].\n\n=== Modeling ===\nDuring his junior year at the [[University of Colorado at Boulder|University of Colorado]] in Boulder, he was discovered by a modeling agent. Since college, he's been a much sought-after model, working in Milan, Paris, Barcelona, London, Sydney, New York, Miami and Los Angeles for such publications as Uomo [[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]], [[GQ]], [[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]] and [[Men's Health]], as well as countless national and international commercials. In addition, he landed various print campaigns for [[Versace]], [[Armani]] and Catalyst Cologne.\n\nHe appeared on an episode of ''[[America's Next Top Model, Cycle 4]]'' in 2005 as a lingerie model in the episode \"The Girl Who Pushes Tyra Over The Edge\".\n\n=== Acting ===\nReturning to the U.S. in spring of 1996, Hillis moved to Los Angeles and landed a role on an episode of ''[[Baywatch Nights]]'' as Jeds.\n\nHis most notable role as an actor came in 2015 on ''General Hospital''\u2019s spin-off ''[[Port Charles]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soapcentral.com/pc/whoswho/jake.php|accessdate=April 18, 2016|work=SoapCentral|title=Jake Marshak}}</ref> as [[Jake Marshak|Dr. Jake Marshak]]. He was on the show from 1997\u20131998 and in May 2006, he substituted for [[Eric Martsolf]] as [[Ethan Winthrop]] on ''[[Passions]]'' when Martsolf took paternity leave for his newborn twin sons. Moreover, he has appeared in dozens of television shows such as ''[[Ugly Betty]]'', ''[[Two and a Half Men]]'', ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation|CSI]]'' and ''[[CSI: Miami]]''. He also has a starring role in the feature film ''[[Propiedad Ajena]].''\n\nHillis played the leading role in the Syfy feature film ''[[Piranhaconda]]'' in 2012.\nHe played Val Walker in ''[[Cowboys vs Dinosaurs]]'' in 2012.\n\n=== Reality Television ===\n\nHillis has done two home improvement/building shows, ''Model Citizen'' and ''[[Get a Grip]]''.\n\nIn the Fall 2007 TV season, Hillis joined the design team on ABC's ''[[Extreme Makeover: Home Edition]]''.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|id=0385032|name=Rib Hillis}}\n* [http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/rib-hillis/265299 Rib Hillis in TV Guide]\n* [http://abc.go.com/primetime/xtremehome/index?pn=bios#t=designer&d=32781 Rib Hillis at ABC]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hillis, Rib}}\n[[Category:1971 births]]\n[[Category:American male soap opera actors]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male models from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:People from Suffern, New York]]\n", "name_user": "Jim856796", "label": "safe", "comment": "\"Rib\" isn't a common hypocorism/diminuitive of \"Robert\", so insert back into lede.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rib_Hillis"}
