{"title_page": "Arman Karamyan", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Arman Karamyan\n| image          =\n| fullname       = \n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1979|11|14|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Yerevan]], [[Armenian SSR]], [[Soviet Union]]<br/><small>(now [[Armenia]])</small>\n| height         = 1.75 m\n| position       = [[Forward (association football)|Striker]] / [[Midfielder#Winger|Left winger]]\n| currentclub    = \n| clubnumber     = \n| youthyears1    =\n| youthclubs1    =\n| years1         = 1996\u20131997\n| clubs1         = [[FC Arabkir Yerevan|Arabkir Yerevan]]\n| caps1          = 7\n| goals1         = 4\n| years2         = 1997\u20131998\n| clubs2         = [[FC Pyunik|Pyunik Yerevan]]\n| caps2          = 23\n| goals2         = 4\n| years3         = 1999\u20132000\n| clubs3         = [[Kilikia F.C.|Kilikia Yerevan]]\n| caps3          = 54\n| goals3         = 35\n| years4         = 2001\u20132002\n| clubs4         = [[FC Pyunik|Pyunik Yerevan]]\n| caps4          = 41\n| goals4         = 57\n| years5         = 2003\n| clubs5         = [[Panachaiki 2005 F.C.|Panachaiki Patras]]\n| caps5          = 15\n| goals5         = 0\n| years6         = 2003\u20132004\n| clubs6         = [[FC Arsenal Kyiv|Arsenal Kyiv]]\n| caps6          = 10\n| goals6         = 1\n| years7         = 2004\u20132006\n| clubs7         = [[FC Rapid Bucure\u015fti|Rapid Bucure\u015fti]]\n| caps7          = 6\n| goals7         = 0\n| years8         = 2005\n| clubs8         = \u2192 [[FC Bra\u015fov]] (loan)\n| caps8          = 9\n| goals8         = 2\n| years9         = 2005\n| clubs9         = \u2192 [[ACF Gloria 1922 Bistri\u021ba|Gloria Bistri\u0163a]] (loan)\n| caps9          = 6\n| goals9         = 0\n| years10        = 2006\n| clubs10        = \u2192 [[FC Bra\u015fov|Bra\u015fov]] (loan)\n| caps10         = 10\n| goals10        = 10\n| years11        = 2006\u20132007\n| clubs11        = [[FC Ceahl\u0103ul Piatra Neam\u021b|Ceahl\u0103ul Piatra Neam\u0163]]\n| caps11         = 13\n| goals11        = 0\n| years12        = 2007\u20132010\n| clubs12        = [[FC Politehnica Timi\u0219oara|Politehnica Timi\u015foara]]\n| caps12         = 50\n| goals12        = 16\n| years13        = 2010\n| clubs13        = [[FC Steaua Bucure\u015fti|Steaua Bucure\u015fti]]\n| caps13         = 13\n| goals13        = 5\n| years14        = 2010\u20132011\n| clubs14        = [[FC Unirea Urziceni|Unirea Urziceni]]\n| caps14         = 5\n| goals14        = 0\n| years15        = 2012\u20132014\n| clubs15        = [[FC Clinceni|Clinceni]]\n| caps15         = 41\n| goals15        = 22\n| years16        = 2016\n| clubs16        = Voin\u021ba Crevedia\n| caps16         = 18\n| goals16        = 9\n| totalcaps = 321\n| totalgoals = 165\n| nationalyears1 = 2000\u20132010\n| nationalteam1  = [[Armenia national football team|Armenia]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 48\n| nationalgoals1 = 5\n| ntupdate       = {{date|2017-07-31}}\n}}\n\n'''Arman Karamyan''' ({{lang-hy|\u0531\u0580\u0574\u0561\u0576 \u0554\u0561\u0580\u0561\u0574\u0575\u0561\u0576}}; born 14 November 1979) is a retired [[Armenia]]n [[association football|footballer]] and former international for the [[Armenia national football team|Armenian national team]]. Arman is the twin brother of fellow football player [[Artavazd Karamyan]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Arabkir===\nArman Karamyan began playing football as a senior in 1996. That year, both he and his older brother [[Artavazd Karamyan]] joined [[Arabkir Yerevan|Arabkir]]. \n\n===Pyunik Yerevan===\nIn 1997, they both made their way to [[FC Pyunik|Pyunik Yerevan]]. Arman was a part of Pyunik when they won the [[Armenian Premier League]] in [[2001 Armenian Premier League|2001]] and [[2002 Armenian Premier League|2002]], the [[Armenian Cup]] in 2002 and [[Armenian Supercup]] in 1997 and 2002.\n\n===Kilikia Yerevan and return to Pyunik Yerevan===\nBoth brothers moved to [[Kilikia F.C.|Kilikia Yerevan]] in 1999 and back to Pyunik in 2001.\n\n===Panachaiki Patras===\nThey both joined the [[Greek Football League|Football League (Greece)]] in 2003 when they both signed with [[Panachaiki 2005 F.C.|Panachaiki Patras]].\n\n===Arsenal Kyiv===\nFrom 2003 to 2004, they both played in [[Ukrainian Premier League]] club [[FC Arsenal Kyiv|Arsenal Kyiv]].\n\n===Rapid Bucure\u015fti===\nArman and Artavazd both joined [[Liga I]] club [[FC Rapid Bucure\u015fti|Rapid Bucure\u015fti]] in 2004. While Arman left that season, Artavazd would remain in the club for a number of seasons.\n\n===Loans to Bra\u015fov and Gloria Bistri\u0163a===\nArman was loaned to other Liga I clubs [[FC Bra\u015fov|Bra\u015fov]] and [[ACF Gloria 1922 Bistri\u021ba|Gloria Bistri\u0163a]] for the 2005 season.\n\n===Second loan to Bra\u015fov===\nHe was loaned to [[FC Bra\u015fov|Bra\u015fov]] again at the start of the 2006 season.\n\n===Ceahl\u0103ul Piatra Neam\u0163===\nArman than officially signed with [[FC Ceahl\u0103ul Piatra Neam\u021b|Ceahl\u0103ul Piatra Neam\u0163]].\n\n===Politehnica Timi\u015foara===\nBoth Arman and Artavazd reunited in the club [[FC Politehnica Timi\u0219oara|Politehnica Timi\u015foara]] in 2007. The next season, the club was a finalist in the [[2008\u201309 Liga I]] championship.\n\n===Steaua Bucure\u015fti===\nThe Karamyan brothers moved to [[FC Steaua Bucure\u015fti|Steaua Bucure\u015fti]] in 2010. In the [[2009\u201310 Liga I|2009\u201310]] season, Arman was selected as the [[Midfielder#Winger|left winger]] of the year. After finishing Liga I for the 2009\u201310 season, the brothers ended their contracts with Steaua Bucure\u015fti. A search began to find the club they would both continue playing football in. But the process of finding a new club was delayed. Later, it was reported that the brothers were in talks with [[FC Bra\u0219ov|Bra\u015fov]]. However, the head coach of Bra\u015fov Daniel Iseyle later stated that the transition of the Karmanyans was unlikely to be completed because of the complexity of the negotiations, which reached a standstill.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ru:\u041f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0433\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0440\u044b \u0441 \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043c\u044f\u043d\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0448\u043b\u0438 \u0432 \u0442\u0443\u043f\u0438\u043a |url=http://www.armsport.am/ru/news/2/48/11376/ |publisher=armsport.am |accessdate=31 March 2013 |language=ru |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100821234259/http://www.armsport.am/ru/news/2/48/11376/ |archivedate=21 August 2010 }}</ref> Talks were later made for the brothers to play for [[FC Astra Giurgiu|Astra Giurgiu]], coached by [[Mihai Stoichi\u021b\u0103]]. But after Stoichi\u021b\u0103 departed from the club, the talks ended. According to an edition of ''TotalFootball'', because of the long search for a new team, the financial conditions for the Karamyan brothers increased to that of a required minimum of 10,000 euros per month. The option that both players finish their playing careers and enter into coaching activities was considered.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ru:\u0411\u0440\u0430\u0442\u044c\u044f \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043c\u044f\u043d\u044b \u043c\u043e\u0433\u0443\u0442 \u0437\u0430\u0432\u0435\u0440\u0448\u0438\u0442\u044c \u043a\u0430\u0440\u044c\u0435\u0440\u0443|url=http://armfootball.com/rus/news/4923/|publisher=ArmFootball.com|accessdate=31 March 2013|language=ru}}</ref>\n\n===Unirea Urziceni===\nIn mid-September 2010, the search was over for Karamyan brothers. The football players signed a contract with and officially moved into [[FC Unirea Urziceni|Unirea Urziceni]].<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ru:\u0411\u0440\u0430\u0442\u044c\u044f \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043c\u044f\u043d \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0448\u043b\u0438 \u0432 \u00ab\u0423\u043d\u0438\u0440\u044e\u00bb |url=http://www.armsport.am/ru/news/2/48/12231/ |publisher=armsport.am |accessdate=31 March 2013 |language=ru |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101121013346/http://www.armsport.am/ru/news/2/48/12231/ |archivedate=21 November 2010 }}</ref> Near the end of a match, Arman made his debut for the club coming in as a substitute for 81tH minute of the game.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ru:\u0410\u0440\u043c\u0430\u043d \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043c\u044f\u043d \u0434\u0435\u0431\u044e\u0442\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b \u0432 \u0441\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0435 \u00ab\u0423\u043d\u0438\u0440\u0438\u00bb |url=http://www.armsport.am/ru/news/2/48/12251/ |publisher=armsport.am |accessdate=31 March 2013 |language=ru |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100921080944/http://www.armsport.am/ru/news/2/48/12251/ |archivedate=21 September 2010 }}</ref>\n\nIn late October 2011, Stoichi\u021b\u0103, who knew firsthand the playing abilities of both brothers, invited them to his current team [[CS Mioveni|Mioveni]]. However, Artavazd decided to retire as a player and go into business.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ru:\u0411\u0440\u0430\u0442\u044c\u044f \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043c\u044f\u043d\u044b \u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0444\u0443\u0442\u0431\u043e\u043b \u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438 \u0431\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0430 |url=http://www.armsport.am/ru/news/2/48/27719/ |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130114171804/http://www.armsport.am/ru/news/2/48/27719/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=14 January 2013 |publisher=armsport.am |accessdate=31 March 2013 |language=ru }}</ref>\n\n===Buftea===\nA year later, Artavazd resumed his career and he and Arman both joined the [[Liga II]] club [[CS Buftea|Buftea]]. In their first meeting, Artavazd scored twice. Arman also scored a goal in their second match.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=hy:\u0531\u0580\u057f\u0561\u057e\u0561\u0566\u0564 \u0554\u0561\u0580\u0561\u0574\u0575\u0561\u0576\u0568 \u057e\u0565\u0580\u0561\u0564\u0561\u0580\u0571\u0565\u056c \u0567 \u0574\u0565\u056e \u0586\u0578\u0582\u057f\u0562\u0578\u056c \u0587 \u0564\u0561\u0580\u0571\u0565\u056c \u0567 \u0564\u0578\u0582\u0562\u056c\u056b \u0570\u0565\u0572\u056b\u0576\u0561\u056f|url=http://armfootball.com/arm/news/23256/artavazd---karamyan-vernulsya-v-bolshoiy-futbol-i-oformil-dubl-video.html|publisher=ArmFootball.com|accessdate=31 March 2013|language=hy}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|script-title=hy:\u0531\u0580\u0574\u0561\u0576 \u0554\u0561\u0580\u0561\u0574\u0575\u0561\u0576\u0568 \u0561\u0579\u0584\u056b \u0567 \u0568\u0576\u056f\u0565\u056c \u00ab\u0534\u056b\u0576\u0561\u0574\u0578-2\u00bb-\u056b \u0564\u0565\u0574 \u056d\u0561\u0572\u0578\u0582\u0574|url=http://armfootball.com/arm/news/23497/arman-karamyan-otlichilsya-v-matche-protiv-dinamo-2.html|publisher=ArmFootball.com|accessdate=31 March 2013|language=hy}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nKaramyan was a member of the [[Armenia national football team|Armenia national team]] and had participated in 49 international matches and scored 5 goals since his debut in an away [[Exhibition game|friendly match]] against [[Guatemala national football team|Guatemala]] on 9 January 2000 ending 1\u20131. In 2010, he left the national team.\n\n==Personal life==\nHe and his brother [[Artavazd Karamyan]] were both football players and have spent nearly their entire careers playing for the same teams.\n\nAt the end 2014 he took the [[Romania]]n citizenship, together with his brother. They are living in Romania with their kids and wives.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sportnews.ro/fratii-gemeni-armeni-arman-si-artiom-karamian-au-primit-cetatenia-romana-dupa-10-ani-petrecuti-tara-noastra-102857.html|title=Karamienii sunt rom\u00e2ni!|publisher=SportNews|date=4 November 2014|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\n==National team statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! colspan=3 | [[Armenia national football team|Armenia national team]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|-\n|2000||8||1\n|-\n|2001||4||0\n|-\n|2002||3||1\n|-\n|2003||7||1\n|-\n|2004||5||2\n|-\n|2005||3||