0 January \u2013 [[English cricket team|England]] defeats [[Australian cricket team|Australia]] 2\u20131 in the [[History of Test cricket (to 1883)#Bligh reclaims the Ashes 1882.2F3|1882\u201383 Test cricket series]], reclaiming \"[[The Ashes]]\" of English cricket.\n*November \u2013 ''Martini-Henry'' wins the [[Melbourne Cup]]\n*2 November \u2013The Northern Rugby Union (later renamed [[Queensland Rugby Union]]) is formed at a meeting in [[Brisbane, Queensland|Brisbane]]\n* Petersham Rugby Union Football Club formed in Sydney NSW\n\n==Births==\n* 12 April \u2013 [[Dally Messenger]], rugby footballer (died 1959)<ref>{{Australian Dictionary of Biography|last=Cunneen|first=Chris|year=1986|id=A100475b|title=Messenger, Herbert Henry (Dally)  (1883\u20131959) |accessdate=22 February 2010}}</ref>\n* 15 April \u2013 [[Stanley Bruce]] (died 1967), 8th [[Prime Minister of Australia]]<ref>{{Australian Dictionary of Biography|last=Radi|first=Heather|year=1979|id=A070460b|title= Bruce, Stanley Melbourne (1883\u20131967)|accessdate=22 February 2010}}</ref>\n* 30 May \u2013 [[Sandy Pearce]] (died 1930), rugby league footballer and boxer<ref>{{Australian Dictionary of Biography|last=Corcoran|first=Kristine|year=1988|id=A110186b|title=Pearce, Sidney Charles (Sandy)  (1883\u20131930)|accessdate=22 February 2010}}</ref>\n* 1 July \u2013 [[Micky Dore]] (died 1910), rugby league footballer\n* 1 September \u2013 [[Robert Graves (rugby)|Robert Graves]] (died 1958), rugby footballer\n* 12 December \u2013 [[William Baylebridge]] (died 1943), poet and short story writer<ref>{{Australian Dictionary of Biography|last=Bonnin|first=Nancy|year=1979|id=A070217b|title=Baylebridge, William  (1883\u20131942) |accessdate=22 February 2010}}</ref>\n\n==Deaths==\n* 5 January \u2013 [[Charles Tompson]] (born 1806), poet\n* 18 August \u2013 [[Roger William Bede Vaughan]] (born 1834), [[Catholic Bishops and Archbishops of Sydney|Archbishop of Sydney]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Years in Australia}